<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>FAQ - PETCON</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/5.3.0/css/bootstrap.min.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header class="text-center mt-4">
            <h1 class="welcome-header">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">1. What is PETCON?</h2>
            <p>PETCON is a platform designed to help find and reunite lost dogs with their worried owners. It utilizes advanced technology, such as IP cameras and machine learning algorithms, to facilitate the search and location of lost pets.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">2. How does PETCON work?</h2>
            <p>PETCON uses strategically placed IP cameras to capture real-time images from areas prone to dog loss. These images are processed using breed classification algorithms to identify specific dogs, and users can access the platform to search for lost pets and receive personalized alerts.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">3. How can I register for PETCON?</h2>
            <p>To register for PETCON, simply click on the "Sign Up" link on the top right corner and fill out the registration form with your personal information.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">4. How can I log in to my PETCON account?</h2>
            <p>You can log in to your PETCON account using your email address and password in the login form after clicking "Login" in the top right corner.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">5. What should I do if I forgot my password?</h2>
            <p>If you forgot your password, you can use the "Forgot password?" option on the login page to reset it.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">6. How can I set up personalized alerts on PETCON?</h2>
            <p>To set up personalized alerts, first you need to login. After that, go to the "Alerts" section in your PETCON account and choose your location and dog breed preferences. You will receive email notifications when lost dogs matching your criteria are detected.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">7. What should I do if I find a lost dog?</h2>
            <p>If you find a lost dog, you can use PETCON to post details about the pet and its location. This will help worried owners find and reunite with their lost pets.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">8. How can I contact the PETCON team?</h2>
            <p>You can contact the PETCON team using the contact form in the "Contact" section of the website, where you can submit inquiries, suggestions, or feedback.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">9. Is PETCON free to use?</h2>
            <p>Yes, PETCON is free for all users. There are no costs associated with registration or using the platform.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-center">10. What should I do if I encounter technical issues with PETCON?</h2>
            <p>If you experience technical issues with PETCON, you can check our help section or contact the technical support team through the contact form. We'll be happy to help you resolve any issues you may have.</p>
        </section>

    </div>
</body>
</html>
